com.canoo.dolphin.collections

Interface ObservableList<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of elements in the list
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, Iterable<E>, List<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObservableArrayList

    public interface ObservableList<E>
extends List<E>
    This interface extends the default List interface and adds the possibility to observe the list. By adding a ListChangeListener (see onChanged(ListChangeListener)) all mutations of the list can be observed. In addition this class provides some convenience methods. The ObservableList interface is part of teh Dolphin Platform model API. Since the lifecylce of models will be managed by the Dolphin Platform the API don't provide a public implementation for this interface. When defining models a developer only need to use the interface like it is already descriped in the Property class. Like the Property a ObservableList can be used in any Dolphin Platform model (see DolphinBean). Example: 
          @DolphinBean
     public class MyModel {

          private ObservableList<String> values;

          public ObservableList<String> getValues() {
              return values;
          }
         
     }

        Subscription onChanged(ListChangeListener<? super E> listener)
